import './About.css';

const About = () => {
  return (
    <div className="about-container">
      <h1>About Me</h1>
      <p>
       I am a third-year B.Tech Computer Science Engineering student at Lovely Professional University (LPU) with a strong interest in software development and problem solving. I enjoy building practical applications and continuously improving my technical skills through hands-on projects and learning.

I have developed a solid foundation in Data Structures and Algorithms and regularly apply these concepts while solving programming problems and designing efficient solutions. My primary programming languages include C++, Java, and JavaScript.

On the development side, I have experience working across the full stack. I have worked with technologies such as React for building interactive front-end interfaces, and Node.js with MongoDB for creating scalable back-end systems and databases. Through this stack, I have built several projects including a Student Management System, an Ayurvedic Diet Management System, and a Task Scheduling Software, where I focused on designing clean architecture and solving real-world problems through code.

In addition to web development, I have also explored Android development using Kotlin, which helped me understand mobile application design and platform-specific development practices.

I am passionate about technology and continuously seek opportunities to learn new tools, frameworks, and concepts. I enjoy turning ideas into functional software and improving my problem-solving abilities through consistent practice and project development. My goal is to grow as a developer by building impactful applications and contributing to meaningful technological solutions.

      </p>

    </div>
  );
};

export default About;
